With that being said, driving pressure (DP) is the difference between the airway pressure at the end of inspiration (plateau pressure, Ppl) and PEEP [7, 13]. In turn, static compliance of the respiratory system (CRS) is the quotient between Vt and driving pressure. Ergo, by simple arithmetic, driving pressure is the quotient between the Vt and CRS of the patient:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
